Sift the flour and salt into a large bowl. Make a well in the middle of the flour.Add the egg, egg yolk and milk to the well in the flour and whisk until the batter is smooth. Leave to rest for a few minutes.Heat a flat griddle or frying pan and rub with vegetable oil. Pour a ladleful of batter into the pan and swirl to coat the base. Cook for 1-2 minutes, then flip and cook on the other side for one minute.Place the pancake on a plate and repeat with the rest of the batter.To serve, fold each pancake into four. Place onto serving plates and serve with raspberries and whipped cream.